WEBVTT

00:01.902 --> 00:04.471 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: The nation's
new attorney
general has spent this day under
growing fire.

00:04.571 --> 00:09.509 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And now, Jeff Sessions says
someone else will
oversee any investigation of
Russian meddling

00:09.610 --> 00:14.548 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in the election and of contacts
between the
Trump campaign and the Russians.

00:14.648 --> 00:16.516 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Lisa Desjardins begins our
coverage.

00:16.617 --> 00:21.421 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
LISA DESJARDINS: The new
attorney general,
three weeks on the job, came to
the Justice

00:21.521 --> 00:24.258 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Department briefing room this
afternoon to
make his statement.

00:24.358 --> 00:28.028 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFF SESSIONS, U.S. Attorney
General: My staff
recommended recusal.

00:28.128 --> 00:34.001 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They said that, since I had
involvement with
the campaign, I should not be
involved in

00:34.101 --> 00:37.237 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
any campaign investigation.

00:37.337 --> 00:41.541 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I have studied the rules and
considered their
comments and evaluation.

00:41.642 --> 00:45.712 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I believe those recommendations
are right
and just.

00:45.812 --> 00:52.352 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Therefore, I have recused myself
in the matters
that deal with the Trump
campaign.

00:52.452 --> 00:56.590 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: This after The
Washington
Post reported that, during the
campaign, when

00:56.690 --> 01:01.561 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Jeff Sessions was a senator and
Trump campaign
adviser, he met with the Russian
ambassador

01:01.662 --> 01:03.497 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to the U.S. twice.

01:03.597 --> 01:08.368 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Then-Senator Sessions had more
than 25 conversations
with foreign ambassadors last
year.

01:08.468 --> 01:11.738 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Two of those were with Sergey
Kislyak, the
Russian envoy.

01:11.838 --> 01:16.476 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
At his news conference, Sessions
took issue
with any suggestion of
impropriety.

01:16.576 --> 01:23.750 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFF SESSIONS: Let me be clear:
I never had
meetings with Russian operatives
or Russian

01:23.850 --> 01:26.086 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
intermediaries about the Trump
campaign.

01:26.186 --> 01:31.625 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
LISA DESJARDINS: He also
defended answers
he gave during his Senate
confirmation.

01:31.725 --> 01:35.295 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Minnesota Democrat Al Franken
cited U.S. intelligence
documents.

01:35.395 --> 01:37.130 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

01:37.230 --> 01:40.767 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
AL FRANKEN (D), Minnesota: These
documents,
also allegedly, say -- quote --
"There was

01:40.867 --> 01:48.208 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
a continuing exchange of
information during
the campaign between Trump
surrogates and

01:48.308 --> 01:51.712 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
intermediaries for the Russian
government."

01:51.812 --> 01:56.483 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFF SESSIONS: Senator Franken,
I'm not aware
of any of those activities.

01:56.583 --> 02:02.889 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I have been called a surrogate
at a time or
two in that campaign, and I did
not have communications

02:02.990 --> 02:04.558 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
with the Russians.

02:04.658 --> 02:07.127 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: This afternoon,
Sessions
said he never meant to be
misleading.

02:07.227 --> 02:13.367 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFF SESSIONS: My reply to the
question of
Senator Franken was honest and
correct as

02:13.467 --> 02:16.203 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I understood it at the time.

02:16.303 --> 02:21.708 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I appreciate that some have
taken the view
that this was a false comment.

02:21.808 --> 02:23.577 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
That is not my intent.

02:23.677 --> 02:24.978 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
That is not correct.

02:25.078 --> 02:27.814 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: But Democrats
in Congress
weren't buying it.

02:27.914 --> 02:29.383 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Senate Minority Leader Chuck
Schumer:

02:29.483 --> 02:31.318 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

02:31.418 --> 02:32.252 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHUCK SCHUMER (D-NY), Minority
Leader: I don't
think that is the way most think
people would

02:32.352 --> 02:33.487 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
interpret it.

02:33.587 --> 02:35.922 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And that's why we need to have a
thorough
investigation.

02:36.023 --> 02:40.327 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Schumer and
House Minority
Leader Nancy Pelosi demanded
that Sessions

02:40.427 --> 02:41.328 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
resign.

02:41.428 --> 02:43.196 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

02:43.296 --> 02:45.966 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHUCK SCHUMER: The standard for
remaining
attorney general and certainly
for conducting

02:46.066 --> 02:48.902 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
investigations is not just, did
you break
the law?

02:49.002 --> 02:49.903 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
You have to be above reproach.

02:50.003 --> 02:51.772 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

02:51.872 --> 02:54.141 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NANCY PELOSI (D-CA), House
Minority Leader:
He has proved that he is
unqualified and unfit

02:54.241 --> 02:56.743 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to serve in that position of
trust.

02:56.843 --> 03:00.847 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Seventeen
Democrats on the
House Judiciary Committee
formally asked for

03:00.947 --> 03:05.952 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a criminal investigation of
Sessions for allegedly
lying to Congress.

03:06.053 --> 03:09.256 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Democrats are also pushing for a
special prosecutor
in the case.

03:09.356 --> 03:11.958 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But there was also pressure from
Republicans.

03:12.059 --> 03:16.396 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Several called for Sessions to
recuse himself
from the Russia investigation
before he eventually

03:16.496 --> 03:18.031 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
did so.

03:18.131 --> 03:21.201 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But Speaker of the House Paul
Ryan played
down such talk.

03:21.301 --> 03:22.536 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

03:22.636 --> 03:23.804 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAUL RYAN (R-WI), Speaker of the
House: Asked
him questions.

03:23.904 --> 03:25.672 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, honestly, we meet with
ambassadors all
the time.

03:25.772 --> 03:30.277 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I mean, I did a reception about
100 yards
that way with like 100
ambassadors last year.

03:30.377 --> 03:34.381 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
LISA DESJARDINS: And this
afternoon, Sessions'
boss weighed in, in Newport
News, Virginia,

03:34.481 --> 03:36.216 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
aboard the aircraft carrier
Gerald R. Ford.

03:36.316 --> 03:37.451 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
QUESTION: Mr. President, do you
still have
confidence in the attorney
general?

03:37.551 --> 03:39.553 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP, President of the
United States:
Total.

03:39.653 --> 03:45.192 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: The president
said he believes
Sessions probably did speak
truthfully to

03:45.292 --> 03:47.094 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the Senate.

03:47.194 --> 03:50.797 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He also said he didn't think
Sessions should
recuse himself, but, 90 minutes
later, the

03:50.897 --> 03:52.833 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
attorney general did just that.

03:52.933 --> 03:57.637 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The revelations come just two
weeks after
then-National Security Adviser
Michael Flynn

03:57.737 --> 03:59.573 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
was forced out.

03:59.673 --> 04:04.377 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He'd told Vice President Mike
Pence that he
didn't meet discuss sanctions
with a Russian

04:04.478 --> 04:07.147 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
official, when, in fact, he had.

04:07.247 --> 04:11.384 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And in a further development,
The New York
Times reported today officials
in the Obama

04:11.485 --> 04:16.690 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
administration rushed to spread
intelligence
of any contacts between the
Trump campaign

04:16.790 --> 04:19.526 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and the Russians before leaving
office.

04:19.626 --> 04:20.594 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Their goal?

04:20.694 --> 04:23.096 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
To ensure a trail remained for
investigators.

04:23.196 --> 04:26.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Lisa
Desjardins joins me
now.

04:26.166 --> 04:29.136 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Lisa, this happened late in the
afternoon,
about a 4:00 press conference.

04:29.236 --> 04:31.972 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What was the reaction to this
from the people
on the Hill that you have spoken
to?

04:32.072 --> 04:34.908 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: There's a full
spectrum of
reaction on Capitol Hill, Hari.

04:35.008 --> 04:39.045 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There are some Republicans who
say they do
not believe that Attorney
General Sessions

04:39.146 --> 04:40.447 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
should have recused himself.

04:40.547 --> 04:42.015 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
These are folks that are his
colleagues.

04:42.115 --> 04:43.517 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They see him as an honest man.

04:43.617 --> 04:46.653 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And they were saying all day
long that he
shouldn't do anything new.

04:46.753 --> 04:50.924 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But there are other Republicans
who will tell
you privately that they are
relieved, that

04:51.024 --> 04:54.761 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
they saw this as a problem for
their party,
especially at a time when
they're trying to

04:54.861 --> 04:57.831 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
focus on other things, like, oh,
the Affordable
Care Act.

04:57.931 --> 05:02.035 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Those Republicans, one told me
privately,
are hoping that this means there
will be a

05:02.135 --> 05:05.972 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
pause in the daily questions
they have been
receiving on Russia.

05:06.072 --> 05:08.942 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And that brings us to the third
reaction up
here, Democrats.

05:09.042 --> 05:10.010 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They have a different plan.

05:10.110 --> 05:12.546 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They do not plan on pausing
these questions.

05:12.646 --> 05:18.852 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, in fact, House and Senate
Minority Leaders
Pelosi and Schumer instantly
sent out responses

05:18.952 --> 05:21.922 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
saying that they are again
demanding a special
prosecutor.

05:22.022 --> 05:27.761 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They say that Attorney General
Sessions' recusal
just adds to the need for a
special prosecutor.

05:27.861 --> 05:29.496 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And they are still calling for
him to resign.

05:29.596 --> 05:31.998 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: All right, so
it sounds
like some critics are doubling
down.

05:32.098 --> 05:36.002 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What about some of the reports
that we also
had later this afternoon about
more meetings

05:36.102 --> 05:38.305 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
between members of the Trump
camp and Russians?

05:38.405 --> 05:40.607 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: These were new
developments
today as well.

05:40.707 --> 05:46.112 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The New York Times reporting,
quoting a White
House official, Hope Hicks, as
confirming

05:46.213 --> 05:52.252 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that Jared Kushner, President
Trump's son-in-law
and a senior adviser, was at a
meeting with

05:52.352 --> 05:57.457 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the Russian ambassador, and
Michael Flynn,
the former national security
adviser, at Trump

05:57.557 --> 05:59.492 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Tower.

05:59.593 --> 06:02.462 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This gets confusing, because now
we're seeing
more and more players here, but
this is significant,

06:02.562 --> 06:06.466 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
because now we're adding more
members of the
Trump team who were meeting with
this Russian

06:06.566 --> 06:08.268 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
ambassador.

06:08.368 --> 06:11.705 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
At that point, it was Kushner,
Flynn and the
ambassador at Trump Tower in
December.

06:11.805 --> 06:17.611 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
That's when the Obama
administration was working
on ramping up sanctions, a very
critical timeline

06:17.711 --> 06:19.512 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
there.

06:19.613 --> 06:22.749 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think overall it just adds
to the map
in this entire kind of
Russia-Trump situation.

06:22.849 --> 06:28.288 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I will say the White House
says that Mr.
Kushner met with many
international dignitaries,

06:28.388 --> 06:30.257 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and the Russian ambassador was
just one.

06:30.357 --> 06:33.360 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: All right,
Lisa Desjardins
joining us from Capitol Hill,
thanks so much.

06:33.460 --> 06:38.465 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In the day's other news: The
president carried
his call for a major military
buildup to a

06:38.565 --> 06:40.467 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
U.S. Navy audience.

06:40.567 --> 06:44.938 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Mr. Trump spoke aboard the newly
built aircraft
carrier Gerald R. Ford in
Newport News, Virginia,

06:45.038 --> 06:46.806 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and touted his plan for Naval
expansion.

06:46.906 --> 06:54.180 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: After years of
endless budget
cuts, that have impaired our
defenses, I am

06:54.281 --> 06:58.451 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
calling for one of the largest
defense spending
increases in history.

06:58.551 --> 07:05.325 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Our military requires sustained,
stable funding
to meet the growing needs placed
on our defense.

07:05.425 --> 07:08.561 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
HARI SREENIVASAN: The
president's draft budget
calls for boosting overall
defense spending

07:08.662 --> 07:11.765 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
by $54 billion, or 10 percent.

07:11.865 --> 07:16.603 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The U.S. struck hard at al-Qaida
militants
today in Yemen, with more than
20 airstrikes.

07:16.703 --> 07:20.006 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Local officials reported at
least nine suspected
militants were killed.

07:20.106 --> 07:24.377 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Pentagon says the strikes
targeted fighters,
weapons and equipment in a
remote mountainous

07:24.477 --> 07:26.179 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
region.

07:26.279 --> 07:31.251 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It follows a raid in January
when a U.S. Navy
SEAL died and a number of Yemeni
civilians

07:31.351 --> 07:33.186 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
were killed.

07:33.286 --> 07:37.057 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Meanwhile, al-Qaida confirmed
today that a
U.S. drone strike killed its
second-in command,

07:37.157 --> 07:40.727 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Abu Al-Khayr Al-Masri, in Syria
last Sunday.

07:40.827 --> 07:45.165 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A suspected U.S. drone strike
killed two Taliban
militants in Northwest Pakistan
today.

07:45.265 --> 07:47.767 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They were hit in a tribal region
near the
Afghan border.

07:47.867 --> 07:52.305 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It is the first such strike
ordered since
President Trump took office.

07:52.405 --> 07:56.743 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
In Syria, the government
announced it has
fully recaptured the ancient
city of Palmyra

07:56.843 --> 07:59.279 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
from the Islamic State group
again.

07:59.379 --> 08:03.083 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Syrian army troops drove out the
militants
for the second time in a year.

08:03.183 --> 08:06.453 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They were backed by Hezbollah
fighters from
Lebanon and Russian airstrikes.

08:06.553 --> 08:11.458 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ISIS fighters have already
destroyed many
of Palmyra's ancient Roman
sites.

08:11.558 --> 08:16.262 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
An international family planning
conference
raised nearly $200 million today
for family

08:16.363 --> 08:18.198 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
planning initiatives.

08:18.298 --> 08:23.103 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That's after President Trump
reinstated a
U.S. ban -- a ban on U.S.
funding for organizations

08:23.203 --> 08:29.275 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
with any link to abortion,
representatives
from some 50 nations at a
conference in Brussels

08:29.376 --> 08:31.211 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
dubbed She Decides.

08:31.311 --> 08:34.547 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ALEXANDER DE CROO, Belgian
Deputy Premier:
I think that the Trump
administration decision

08:34.647 --> 08:36.449 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
is the wrong decision.

08:36.549 --> 08:47.093 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And I have never seen any
evidence that supports
that decision, but we have a
voice and we

08:47.193 --> 08:48.995 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
have a choice.

08:49.095 --> 08:51.765 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Conference
organizers say
the U.S. funding cutoff left a
global shortfall

08:51.865 --> 08:55.902 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of about $600 million for family
planning
efforts.

08:56.002 --> 08:59.873 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Back in this country, the
Environmental Protection
Agency dropped a requirement
that oil and

08:59.973 --> 09:03.743 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
gas interests report information
on methane
emissions.

09:03.843 --> 09:06.479 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Obama administration issued
that rule
in November.

09:06.579 --> 09:10.784 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In a statement, the new EPA
administrator,
Scott Pruitt, said withdrawing
the rule will

09:10.884 --> 09:15.121 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ease burdens on business, while
he conducts
a full review.

