22:10.629 --> 22:13.899 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Leave aside whether there's
anything to it
or not, those questions are
there.

22:13.999 --> 22:16.535 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There's an evidentiary base for
raising them.

22:16.635 --> 22:23.275 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it's in that context that
the meeting
with Ambassador Kislyak gains
salience and

22:23.375 --> 22:26.512 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
prominence and stands out and is
worth talking
about.

22:26.612 --> 22:28.414 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I think it's entirely that.

22:28.514 --> 22:34.820 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think, ultimately, we will
