this?

24:01.073 --> 24:05.678 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MICHAEL MUKASEY: A special
prosecutor would
have to specially prosecute a
crime.

24:05.778 --> 24:09.915 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so far as I'm aware, nobody
has identified
any crime that was committed
here.

24:10.015 --> 24:12.418 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We don't have people who are
independent of
a government.

24:12.518 --> 24:16.488 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We have a Constitution that
establishes three
branches of government.

24:16.588 --> 24:17.523 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
One is Article I.

24:17.623 --> 24:18.524 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
That's the Congress.

24:18.624 --> 24:19.525 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Article II is the executive.

24:19.625 --> 24:20.526 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And Article III is the
judiciary.

24:20.626 --> 24:22.494 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You have got to be in one or the
other.

24:22.594 --> 24:26.365 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There's no such thing as a
free-flying independent
investigation.

24:26.465 --> 24:33.539 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You can have an investigation
that's conducted
by a special counsel, if that's
warranted,

24:33.639 --> 24:38.010 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
but first somebody has to
identify the commission
of a crime and identify evidence
of a crime.

24:38.110 --> 24:39.645 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
